Hydro-Eakly HS: One of the most decorated players ever signed by the SWOSU Golf program...Ranked third in the state of Oklahoma (all classes) by the Junior Golf Scoreboard...National ranking is 36th in the Class of 2016 and 73rd among all high school prospects...According to that same outlet, he is the highest ranked player from the Class of 2016 to have signed with an NCAA Division II program...Four-year member of the golf team at Hydro-Eakly High School, where he has also played basketball and baseball throughout his career...Had four top-five finishes in the 2015 Oklahoma Junior Golf Tour (OJGT) Fall Series, including a win at the Lincoln Park Junior Classic with round scores of 63 and 69...Also a member of the victorious Team Oklahoma in the 2015 Red River Challenge against a team from Texas.

Previous: Son of Terry and Pendra Cook...Second-generation Bulldog student-athlete after both of his parents previously competed at SWOSU...His father, Terry Cook, was a member of the SWOSU Baseball team and his mother Pendra (Hamar) Cook, was a member of the Lady Bulldogs 1985 National Championship basketball team.
